author: cmpilato
msg: Clean up an old bit of API nastiness which prevented implementations
of the svn_fs_get_locks_callback_t callback from performing additional
FS operations in BDB-backed repositories.  Having svn_fs_get_locks2()
already revved for 1.7 makes this a good time to fix this old bug.
* subversion/include/svn_fs.h
(svn_fs_get_locks2): Add a note about the transient nature of locks
with respect to how this function reports them.  Move a warning
about BDB implementation details which prevents callers from
interacting with the filesystem from within their callback
implementations...
(svn_fs_get_locks): ...to here, and note that it only affects
Subversion 1.6 and prior.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_base/lock.c
(spool_locks_info): New helper callback function.
(struct locks_get_args): Remove 'get_locks_func' and 'get_locks_baton'
members; add 'spool_file' member.
(txn_body_get_locks): Use spool_locks_info/spool_file now for the
callback functions passed to svn_fs_bdb__locks_get().
(svn_fs_base__get_locks): Rewrite this function to use a custom
callback to spool lock information to a disk tempfile instead a
BDB trail, then read that information back and pass it to the
caller outside the trail.
* contrib/hook-scripts/remove-zombie-locks.py
(RepositoryZombieLockRemover.run): Use svn_fs_get_locks2() if it's
available; fall back to the previous code otherwise.
